1
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:18,326
Jimmy, the flowers were a bad idea.

2
00:00:18,385 --> 00:00:20,126
I shouldn't even be here.

3
00:00:20,187 --> 00:00:23,100
Don't be like that. There he is.

4
00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:29,140
Ten hours on a bus from Montreal,

5
00:00:29,196 --> 00:00:31,733
my roids are screaming blue murder.

6
00:00:31,999 --> 00:00:34,138
Well, welcome home, Mickey.

7
00:00:36,403 --> 00:00:38,815
We need to talk. Where's your car?

8
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,521
In the lot, down by 9th.

9
00:00:47,915 --> 00:00:50,452
Look, you're gonna have to take a cab.

10
00:00:50,517 --> 00:00:52,326
Roseanne, I'm sorry.

11
00:00:57,024 --> 00:00:58,662
What about the USB account?

12
00:00:58,725 --> 00:00:59,897
Empty.

13
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:01,871
They're all, except Trust
House and Citibank.

14
00:01:01,929 --> 00:01:03,738
Those I managed to close
before he got to them.

15
00:01:03,797 --> 00:01:05,504
I put the money in a safety deposit box.

16
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:07,102
Son of a bitch!

17
00:01:08,201 --> 00:01:11,410
And Dougie did all this by himself?

18
00:01:11,538 --> 00:01:13,347
Just don't hurt him.

19
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:20,155
Mickey, I didn't know it was yours.

20
00:01:21,848 --> 00:01:23,452
Who did you think it belonged to,

21
00:01:23,517 --> 00:01:25,588
you worthless twit, Santa Claus?

22
00:01:25,686 --> 00:01:29,259
You don't understand. This is the
most important thing in my life.

23
00:01:29,323 --> 00:01:31,360
That money is my life!

24
00:01:31,692 --> 00:01:33,171
And I want it back,

25
00:01:33,226 --> 00:01:35,729
every penny, or I swear to God,

26
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:38,072
I'll take it out of your hide.

27
00:01:39,032 --> 00:01:40,102
Mmm?

28
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,214
You've worked too hard for this.

29
00:01:49,376 --> 00:01:50,753
Maybe I should just give it back.

30
00:01:50,811 --> 00:01:52,449
Baby, you're slipping.

31
00:01:52,512 --> 00:01:53,855
Let me call them.

32
00:01:56,383 --> 00:01:59,421
Look, Doug, we need their help.

33
00:02:06,627 --> 00:02:08,106
Doug's apartment is empty.

34
00:02:08,161 --> 00:02:10,300
Nobody's seen him since yesterday.

35
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:14,707
His mother'll know where he is.

36
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:24,645
He called her.

37
00:02:26,346 --> 00:02:28,553
I promised her he wouldn't get hurt.

38
00:02:28,615 --> 00:02:32,119
Seabreeze Motel in Montauk, Room 114.

39
00:02:41,028 --> 00:02:42,371
Excuse me.

40
00:02:43,163 --> 00:02:44,699
You're excused.

41
00:02:48,402 --> 00:02:50,541
Stand up, you son of a bitch!

42
00:03:50,497 --> 00:03:52,875
The old man, Mickey Connelly,
owns this place.

43
00:03:52,933 --> 00:03:54,469
His son Jimmy used it as an office

44
00:03:54,534 --> 00:03:55,774
when he was out of the country.

45
00:03:55,836 --> 00:03:57,611
The old man was ducking a RICO indictment

46
00:03:57,671 --> 00:03:59,150
for bookmaking on the internet.

47
00:03:59,206 --> 00:04:02,119
Yeah, well, his legal troubles are over now.

48
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:04,578
Got a murder here,

49
00:04:04,644 --> 00:04:06,419
suicide there. He ate the gun.

50
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,551
Cleaning service found them this morning.

51
00:04:08,615 --> 00:04:10,993
Time of death sometime last night.

52
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:12,889
- Thanks.
- All right.

53
00:04:13,019 --> 00:04:14,828
Can I get a pair of tweezers please?

54
00:04:14,888 --> 00:04:18,927
This must be some of that father-son
bonding I've heard so much about.

55
00:04:20,293 --> 00:04:22,569
These cuts were made before he died,

56
00:04:22,629 --> 00:04:25,337
but for some reason they were untreated.

57
00:04:29,069 --> 00:04:31,606
I'll be over here while you do that.

58
00:04:38,912 --> 00:04:40,687
It's frosted glass.

59
00:04:47,587 --> 00:04:48,793
He has

60
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:54,735
abrasions delicately around
the sides of his mouth.

61
00:04:57,931 --> 00:04:59,911
Well, he was gagged.

62
00:04:59,966 --> 00:05:02,446
Explains why he didn't answer his phone.

63
00:05:02,502 --> 00:05:03,742
He's got voice-mail.

64
00:05:03,804 --> 00:05:06,250
The lab can retrieve the messages.

65
00:05:09,709 --> 00:05:11,382
Mickey's passport.

66
00:05:12,579 --> 00:05:16,083
Irish customs entry stamp
dated November last year.

67
00:05:16,416 --> 00:05:19,090
Exit stamp dated two weeks ago.

68
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,194
Having fun?

69
00:05:21,254 --> 00:05:23,962
I'm listening. He left Ireland two weeks ago.

70
00:05:24,024 --> 00:05:27,062
Canadian customs stamp,
also from two weeks ago.

71
00:05:27,127 --> 00:05:28,538
No US stamp.

72
00:05:29,329 --> 00:05:32,833
Make a note to the ME
to check for ocular fluids.

73
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:35,476
His eyes are dry and irritated.

74
00:05:35,535 --> 00:05:37,310
The mucus is thick.

75
00:05:38,705 --> 00:05:41,743
Could be from sleep deprivation.

76
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:45,213
And he's dehydrated.

77
00:05:45,278 --> 00:05:47,781
His cuticles have shrunk.

78
00:05:48,481 --> 00:05:51,587
Maybe Junior kept him on ice
before killing him.

79
00:05:53,119 --> 00:05:54,792
Except that Junior

80
00:05:57,057 --> 00:05:58,900
shows the same signs.

81
00:06:01,695 --> 00:06:03,333
Mickey had to have a damn good reason

82
00:06:03,396 --> 00:06:05,672
to come back and risk getting
pinched on a fugitive warrant.

83
00:06:05,732 --> 00:06:06,904
How's $2 million bucks?

84
00:06:06,967 --> 00:06:09,607
That's what the DA's always figured
he had stashed away somewhere.

85
00:06:09,669 --> 00:06:10,943
Works for me.

86
00:06:11,004 --> 00:06:13,041
The old man found out the
kid was skimming from him,

87
00:06:13,106 --> 00:06:15,017
they got their Irish up.

88
00:06:15,075 --> 00:06:17,248
I don't think that they got anything up.

89
00:06:17,310 --> 00:06:19,654
The ME found elevated levels of sodium,

90
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:22,057
urea, nitrogen in the eye mucus,

91
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:25,289
kidney and liver enzymes
outside the normal range.

92
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:27,759
Stomach and the bowels empty.

93
00:06:28,021 --> 00:06:31,764
Now, the Connellys, they were starved,

94
00:06:31,825 --> 00:06:34,271
sleep deprived, dehydrated.

95
00:06:34,327 --> 00:06:35,704
They sound like POWs.

96
00:06:35,762 --> 00:06:37,673
The ME also found minute traces of duct tape

97
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:40,177
around the ankles and wrists of both men.

98
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:44,204
The tech's got the code for Mickey's
voice-mail. His son's birth date.

99
00:06:47,107 --> 00:06:49,485
“It's Roseanne again, calling for Jimmy.

100
00:06:49,542 --> 00:06:51,613
“It's been a week. I need to hear from you.

101
00:06:51,678 --> 00:06:52,679
“Just call me.”

102
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:56,082
Roseanne would be Jimmy's wife.

103
00:06:56,149 --> 00:06:57,753
Last Wednesday.

104
00:06:58,518 --> 00:07:01,158
It's a week since she's heard from him.

105
00:07:01,855 --> 00:07:04,768
You think she would've filed
a missing persons report.

106
00:07:08,361 --> 00:07:10,341
I thought he was away on business.

107
00:07:10,397 --> 00:07:13,207
I didn't even know he was with his father.

108
00:07:13,934 --> 00:07:16,141
You've been camping out in here?

109
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:18,746
Andy fell asleep watching a video.

110
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:20,216
I didn't wanna move him.

111
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:23,550
I noticed that your bedrooms,
they face the street.

112
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:33,295
Is it safer back here?

113
00:07:34,554 --> 00:07:35,658
You're terrified.

114
00:07:35,722 --> 00:07:38,703
Anybody that has the front to
kill Mickey Connelly and his son

115
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:40,999
might just come after you, too.

116
00:07:51,438 --> 00:07:53,543
You knew Jimmy was in trouble.

117
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:55,779
Maybe you had something to do with it?

118
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,783
He called Thursday.

119
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:07,555
He tried to pretend everything
was okay, but I knew better.

120
00:08:07,620 --> 00:08:08,894
Where was he?

121
00:08:08,955 --> 00:08:12,402
He was with Mickey. He said he'd be home soon.

122
00:08:12,459 --> 00:08:15,531
There was some problem,
some money was missing.

123
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:18,839
He called you just to check in?

124
00:08:18,965 --> 00:08:22,845
No, he wanted Andy's Social Security
number. He didn't say why.

125
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:29,279
Your son have a bank account?

126
00:08:33,046 --> 00:08:35,117
They opened an account
for the kid when he was born.

127
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:38,060
Last month Jimmy got a safe
deposit box under the account.

128
00:08:38,118 --> 00:08:40,826
The bank says he emptied the box 2 days ago.

129
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:43,390
2 days ago he was dead. So
who emptied the box?

130
00:08:43,456 --> 00:08:45,595
We're checking the bank security tapes.

131
00:08:47,560 --> 00:08:48,766
That's him.

132
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,437
We know this guy?

133
00:08:51,498 --> 00:08:53,478
These are the left ears of both men.

134
00:08:54,667 --> 00:08:56,078
Same shape.

135
00:08:58,338 --> 00:09:00,079
Similar lobes.

136
00:09:00,607 --> 00:09:03,247
Ear structure patterns run in families.

137
00:09:04,944 --> 00:09:06,753
Especially siblings.

138
00:09:14,587 --> 00:09:15,930
Want some?

139
00:09:19,626 --> 00:09:21,663
He'll meet you tomorrow
when they break for lunch.

140
00:09:22,195 --> 00:09:24,471
Doug, it's almost over now.

141
00:09:24,531 --> 00:09:27,535
No one can ever tell you what to do again.

142
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:32,748
His name is Douglas Morgan.

143
00:09:32,806 --> 00:09:34,752
He's Mickey's son by his second ex-wife.

144
00:09:34,808 --> 00:09:35,809
Jimmy's half-brother.

145
00:09:35,875 --> 00:09:37,013
How come we never heard of him?

146
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:39,819
Well, there's no record he's ever been
involved in his father's business.

147
00:09:39,879 --> 00:09:41,790
Just a couple of misdemeanor forgeries.

148
00:09:41,848 --> 00:09:43,691
He's been a pipsqueak up until now.

149
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,922
You like this guy.

150
00:09:44,984 --> 00:09:47,396
Well, a nobody who scammed the scam artist?

151
00:09:47,454 --> 00:09:48,694
I'd buy him a drink.

152
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,063
First, you have to find him.

153
00:09:50,123 --> 00:09:54,037
He moved out of his last known 3 years
ago. No job since last winter.

154
00:09:54,094 --> 00:09:58,236
Credit report says he got 5 credit
cards in the last 4 months.

155
00:09:59,232 --> 00:10:02,805
They never learn. If you
don't want to be found, pay cash.

156
00:10:06,272 --> 00:10:08,616
Mr. Morgan, he checked out last Monday.

157
00:10:08,675 --> 00:10:10,086
He was here for a couple of weeks.

158
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:11,315
By himself?

159
00:10:11,377 --> 00:10:12,981
He had visitors.

160
00:10:14,714 --> 00:10:17,217
No, I didn't notice those two.

161
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,318
Who did you notice?

162
00:10:18,384 --> 00:10:22,696
Well, this one young man
with blond hair, goatee.

163
00:10:22,755 --> 00:10:25,998
He spent a lot of time parked
out here in a chair, reading.

164
00:10:26,059 --> 00:10:28,039
Well, you'd think he'd be warmer inside.

165
00:10:28,094 --> 00:10:31,735
I figured Mr. Morgan had company

166
00:10:31,798 --> 00:10:34,506
and this fellow was giving him his privacy.

167
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:36,513
Well, that's one way to look at it.

168
00:10:39,606 --> 00:10:42,280
This room is very clean.

169
00:10:44,077 --> 00:10:45,715
There's no marks.

170
00:10:48,214 --> 00:10:49,818
No fingerprints.

171
00:10:50,283 --> 00:10:51,728
Same story here.

172
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:53,491
We keep things tidy.

173
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:57,133
Anybody stay here since Mr. Morgan left?

174
00:10:57,724 --> 00:10:58,725
Nah.

175
00:10:58,791 --> 00:11:01,271
We don't get a lot of traffic
out here after Labor Day.

176
00:11:01,327 --> 00:11:03,637
When did they replace the shower door?

177
00:11:05,131 --> 00:11:06,508
We didn't.

178
00:11:12,372 --> 00:11:15,785
There's lime encrustation

179
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:18,618
and soap residue on this door.

180
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,182
And there's none on this one

181
00:11:22,248 --> 00:11:25,889
and the caulking is still soft.

182
00:11:27,353 --> 00:11:30,493
This shower door was broken,
and they replaced it.

183
00:11:30,557 --> 00:11:32,400
The frosted glass in Jimmy's arm.

184
00:11:32,458 --> 00:11:34,028
They were here.

185
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,607
They were kept here for two weeks.

186
00:11:38,331 --> 00:11:40,174
Two men in a tub.

187
00:11:46,139 --> 00:11:48,415
Last year, when Mickey went on the lam,

188
00:11:48,474 --> 00:11:52,115
a dozen bank accounts were opened using
Doug Morgan's Social Security number.

189
00:11:52,178 --> 00:11:55,455
Within two months, there was nearly
$2 million dollars in those accounts.

190
00:11:55,515 --> 00:11:58,223
Mickey hid the money under Doug's
name without telling Doug,

191
00:11:58,284 --> 00:12:00,093
figuring no one would look there.

192
00:12:00,153 --> 00:12:01,223
Somehow Dougie found out.

193
00:12:01,287 --> 00:12:04,291
Starting 4 months ago, he emptied
all but 2 of the accounts.

194
00:12:04,357 --> 00:12:08,134
Those 2 accounts were closed the same
day Jimmy opened the safe deposit box.

195
00:12:08,194 --> 00:12:11,107
We think that Jimmy got wind
of what was going on

196
00:12:11,164 --> 00:12:13,110
and got the money out before Doug did.

197
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:15,271
And put it in the safe deposit box.

198
00:12:15,768 --> 00:12:17,770
So Dougie tortured his father and his brother

199
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:19,817
just to squeeze the last dollar out of them?

200
00:12:19,872 --> 00:12:21,909
Well, the last $200,000.

201
00:12:21,975 --> 00:12:23,454
What the hell is wrong with this kid?

202
00:12:23,509 --> 00:12:25,546
Didn't daddy spend enough
time playing catch with him?

203
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:27,387
Or he got too much attention from his mother.

204
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:30,860
His last parole report says he was
living with her as of 3 years ago.

205
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:32,294
How sweet.

206
00:12:36,222 --> 00:12:38,828
Dougie thought he had a God-given right

207
00:12:38,891 --> 00:12:40,962
to freeload off his mother.

208
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:45,440
Uh-uh.

209
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:46,499
Don't walk there.

210
00:12:46,566 --> 00:12:48,876
- You're gonna make dirt on my carpet here.
- Yeah.

211
00:12:48,935 --> 00:12:51,279
Put these on. I got them at the hospital.

212
00:12:52,205 --> 00:12:54,685
Put them over your feet.

213
00:12:55,642 --> 00:12:57,679
There's only 3 of them.

214
00:12:57,744 --> 00:13:00,247
Well, someone could sit on a chair.

215
00:13:04,584 --> 00:13:07,394
This is a one bedroom, right?

216
00:13:07,453 --> 00:13:08,830
Mmm-hmm.

217
00:13:09,856 --> 00:13:11,460
Where did Doug sleep?

218
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:14,266
Where do you think? On the couch.

219
00:13:15,862 --> 00:13:17,341
I used to have a bigger place,

220
00:13:17,397 --> 00:13:20,276
but after I got out of the hospital

221
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:23,280
cleaning a big place didn't appeal to me.

222
00:13:24,203 --> 00:13:27,116
What about his father, Mickey?
You been in touch with him?

223
00:13:27,173 --> 00:13:29,414
What do I want with that louse?

224
00:13:29,842 --> 00:13:33,255
A louse who knows his way to your heart.

225
00:13:39,719 --> 00:13:41,027
Thank you.

226
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,567
That's $73.

227
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:48,105
It's a bit expensive.

228
00:13:52,565 --> 00:13:55,011
I mean, unless it's Canadian dollars.

229
00:13:55,068 --> 00:13:56,979
Did Mickey drop it off?

230
00:13:57,270 --> 00:14:01,082
I wouldn't set foot in the
same room with that man,

231
00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:06,116
unless it was to go to his wake.

232
00:14:07,580 --> 00:14:09,116
Just your luck.

233
00:14:09,849 --> 00:14:12,227
He was found dead 4 days ago.

234
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:15,825
Oh...

235
00:14:17,223 --> 00:14:19,100
Dear Mary. Oh.

236
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:29,039
What about his boy, Jimmy?

237
00:14:30,837 --> 00:14:32,748
Why, you like Jimmy?

238
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:36,884
He was decent enough.

239
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:40,221
Hadn't been for Jimmy,

240
00:14:41,814 --> 00:14:44,886
Dougie wouldn't have even
known he had a father.

241
00:14:46,219 --> 00:14:48,256
Jimmy brought this to you?

242
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:52,193
Came over looking for Doug?

243
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:57,771
And you knew where he was, because
Doug keeps in touch with his mother.

244
00:14:57,897 --> 00:14:59,001
Yeah.

245
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:05,177
He told me if Jimmy comes asking for him,

246
00:15:06,272 --> 00:15:08,013
to say where he is.

247
00:15:10,042 --> 00:15:12,044
And when Jimmy left here,

248
00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:15,983
you called Doug and told him
that Jimmy was on the way?

249
00:15:16,249 --> 00:15:18,923
Dougie wouldn't hurt Jimmy. He loved him!

250
00:15:19,352 --> 00:15:21,389
We still need to find him.

251
00:15:21,454 --> 00:15:23,832
Mickey left a lot of money behind.

252
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:27,431
Really?

253
00:15:28,728 --> 00:15:32,767
You mean, like clean money
that could go to Dougie?

254
00:15:33,366 --> 00:15:35,004
If we can find him.

255
00:15:36,235 --> 00:15:38,272
I don't have his address.

256
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:46,652
It's in Brooklyn. It's a sublet.

257
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:50,626
He said over on Ovington.
A nice, bright place.

258
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:52,287
You been?

259
00:15:52,418 --> 00:15:54,193
He sent the picture.

260
00:15:56,489 --> 00:15:58,127
No return address.

261
00:15:58,324 --> 00:15:59,598
Bird seed.

262
00:16:00,893 --> 00:16:03,669
We just ask the neighborhood
bird seed store.

263
00:16:03,729 --> 00:16:07,108
Look, through the window,
across the street, on the roof.

