00:31:00,625 --> 00:31:02,662
Yes, because you can't trust the past.

522
00:31:02,728 --> 00:31:06,676
There's what happened, and what
you tell yourself happened.

523
00:31:07,132 --> 00:31:08,543
It was holding me back.

524
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,079
Holding you back from what?

525
00:31:10,135 --> 00:31:11,341
From...

526
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:14,439
From being extraordinary.

527
00:31:17,809 --> 00:31:21,882
It's hard to explain if you
haven't been through GraceNote.

528
00:31:21,947 --> 00:31:23,449
Yes. They don't get it.

529
00:31:23,515 --> 00:31:27,361
It was worth a lot to you, and you
showed your appreciation with gifts.

530
00:31:27,419 --> 00:31:29,660
The money that you took from
your father, it wasn't for you,

531
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:31,826
you gave it to GraceNote.

532
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:33,267
As a gift.

533
00:31:33,325 --> 00:31:36,329
Did Mr. Fuller know
where the money came from?

534
00:31:37,062 --> 00:31:39,508
I told him my family gave it to me.

535
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:41,711
Doug, you remember the girl from the bank?

536
00:31:41,767 --> 00:31:44,475
Her name was Lena. You met
her at GraceNote, right?

537
00:31:45,804 --> 00:31:47,477
She was taking classes with me.

538
00:31:47,539 --> 00:31:50,986
She helped you decide to make
those gifts to Randall Fuller.

539
00:31:51,042 --> 00:31:53,283
We talked about it, but I decided.

540
00:31:53,345 --> 00:31:56,986
Randall Fuller used Lena to convince
you to give that money to GraceNote.

541
00:31:57,048 --> 00:32:00,154
He manipulated you into killing
your father and brother.

542
00:32:00,218 --> 00:32:03,222
No, no, Lena is in love with me.

543
00:32:03,288 --> 00:32:06,599
She decided to be with me.
She made that decision.

544
00:32:10,061 --> 00:32:12,803
Fuller makes the decisions.

545
00:32:14,566 --> 00:32:16,170
That's not true.

546
00:32:16,668 --> 00:32:18,739
Doug, listen to me.

547
00:32:19,538 --> 00:32:23,315
Lena is dead. She committed
suicide last weekend.

548
00:32:25,710 --> 00:32:28,088
You see how her lips are chapped?

549
00:32:28,847 --> 00:32:31,384
The cracked cuticles on her fingers?

550
00:32:35,821 --> 00:32:39,769
Those are the same things we found
on your dad and your brother.

551
00:32:40,592 --> 00:32:42,594
Lena was denied sleep,

552
00:32:43,228 --> 00:32:45,230
food, water.

553
00:32:47,432 --> 00:32:49,469
Doug, he broke her.

554
00:32:49,534 --> 00:32:50,569
It's not true.

555
00:32:50,635 --> 00:32:52,137
He drove her to suicide.

556
00:32:52,204 --> 00:32:55,185
It's bad programming. It's
just a story from your past.

557
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:56,310
Doug, it's what happened.

558
00:32:56,374 --> 00:32:57,717
No! You...

559
00:32:57,943 --> 00:33:01,083
It's how you see it.

560
00:33:01,146 --> 00:33:03,183
It's the story you tell.

561
00:33:03,248 --> 00:33:04,989
It's how you see it.

562
00:33:05,050 --> 00:33:07,929
It's not the way it is.

563
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:11,365
You can't differentiate one
thing from another, you...

564
00:33:18,129 --> 00:33:19,767
I know how it is.

565
00:33:19,998 --> 00:33:21,272
I get it.

566
00:33:22,234 --> 00:33:24,578
You don't. You're not clear.

567
00:33:30,775 --> 00:33:33,779
I'm getting a sense my client
might be amending his plea.

568
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:36,792
Not guilty by reason of mental disease?

569
00:33:40,585 --> 00:33:42,360
I don't know about an insanity defense,

570
00:33:42,420 --> 00:33:46,163
but his credibility as a witness
against Fuller is doubtful.

571
00:33:46,691 --> 00:33:48,932
Assuming he'd even testify against Fuller.

572
00:33:48,994 --> 00:33:53,136
Must be frustrating,
a mind even you can't unlock.

573
00:33:53,265 --> 00:33:54,972
Well, let's get someone who can.

574
00:33:55,033 --> 00:33:57,877
The person who locked it in the first place.

575
00:34:02,274 --> 00:34:04,413
On mike: your life, your day. Thank you.

576
00:34:07,746 --> 00:34:09,248
- Mr. Fuller...
- I have a car waiting.

577
00:34:09,314 --> 00:34:11,555
We'll take you wherever you like.

578
00:34:11,616 --> 00:34:13,721
We asked you if you knew
a man named Doug Morgan.

579
00:34:13,785 --> 00:34:16,026
He attended your seminars,
but you didn't remember him.

580
00:34:16,087 --> 00:34:17,566
Right, I was in a hurry.

581
00:34:17,622 --> 00:34:18,828
You mean, you remember him now?

582
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:21,131
Oh, yes, of course. He made
a large donation to GraceNote.

583
00:34:21,192 --> 00:34:22,967
He told us a little over $2,000,000.

584
00:34:23,028 --> 00:34:25,599
Yeah, somewhere in that neighborhood.
Why, is there a problem?

585
00:34:25,664 --> 00:34:29,168
Yes, see, Doug Morgan stole that money
from his father's bookmaking operation.

586
00:34:29,234 --> 00:34:30,577
I had no idea.

587
00:34:30,635 --> 00:34:34,208
The girl we asked about, that student
volunteer, Lena Caruso, she helped him.

588
00:34:34,272 --> 00:34:36,809
"Helped," that's a bit of an
understatement. She manipulated him.

589
00:34:36,875 --> 00:34:38,183
I'm really sorry to hear it.

590
00:34:38,243 --> 00:34:39,722
You don't know how sorry.

591
00:34:39,811 --> 00:34:42,314
Because the money is proceeds
from an illegal enterprise.

592
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:43,381
The bookmaking.

593
00:34:43,448 --> 00:34:45,553
The DA is moving to seize it
under the RICO act.

594
00:34:45,617 --> 00:34:47,790
We're here to serve you with the papers.

595
00:34:48,853 --> 00:34:52,198
This money was a gift.
You can ask Mr. Morgan.

596
00:34:53,024 --> 00:34:56,597
Well, between us, Mr. Morgan isn't
making a lot of sense right now.

597
00:34:56,661 --> 00:35:00,234
I'm sure your lawyer can work out
a repayment schedule with the DA.

598
00:35:00,665 --> 00:35:03,077
But this money has been committed.

599
00:35:03,134 --> 00:35:04,977
Look, we're innocent victims here.

600
00:35:05,036 --> 00:35:06,572
You know what, to tell you the truth,

601
00:35:06,638 --> 00:35:09,949
I don't care if you keep the money or not.

602
00:35:10,108 --> 00:35:13,885
Right now, we have a problem with Mr. Morgan.

603
00:35:14,446 --> 00:35:15,823
He confessed to the killing.

604
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:17,484
He confessed to stealing the money.

605
00:35:17,549 --> 00:35:19,825
But right now, his present mental state,

606
00:35:19,884 --> 00:35:22,057
I don't think his confession's gonna hold up.

607
00:35:22,854 --> 00:35:26,301
Mr. Morgan was pretty unstable to start with.

608
00:35:27,759 --> 00:35:31,172
Well, I mean, if you just have
a look at him for yourself,

609
00:35:31,229 --> 00:35:34,438
maybe you'll be able to
straighten him out for us.

610
00:35:34,799 --> 00:35:36,938
And if I straighten him out?

611
00:35:37,235 --> 00:35:40,910
I'm sure the DA wouldn't
have a problem with

612
00:35:40,972 --> 00:35:42,645
taking a look at your money problem.

613
00:35:42,707 --> 00:35:44,653
You can't promise that!

614
00:35:46,211 --> 00:35:49,420
I don't want him skipping out
on an insanity plea.

615
00:35:51,216 --> 00:35:53,196
I'll fix it with the DA.

616
00:35:54,786 --> 00:35:56,561
Just think about it.

617
00:36:03,728 --> 00:36:05,833
The DA said that if you
help them with Morgan,

618
00:36:05,897 --> 00:36:07,899
they won't push for restitution.

619
00:36:08,133 --> 00:36:10,636
What if we just gave them the money outright?

620
00:36:10,702 --> 00:36:12,978
They'll still insist on an audit.

621
00:36:17,142 --> 00:36:18,951
If I'm unsuccessful,

622
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:22,014
if Morgan ends up more unstable than before,

623
00:36:24,082 --> 00:36:26,119
do I still get to keep the money?

624
00:36:27,519 --> 00:36:30,591
According to the DA, all
you have to do is try.

625
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:42,244
Mr. Fuller.

626
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:43,677
Hello, Doug.

627
00:36:43,935 --> 00:36:45,846
Why don't you sit here.

628
00:36:51,843 --> 00:36:54,687
You've been going through
a challenging time, Doug.

629
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:56,921
I'd like to assist you.

630
00:36:57,382 --> 00:36:59,919
Mr. Cooper, you've explained to your client

631
00:36:59,984 --> 00:37:02,123
that we're prepared to accept his claim

632
00:37:02,187 --> 00:37:04,565
of sole responsibility for the two murders?

633
00:37:04,622 --> 00:37:06,602
Yes, Mr. Carver, I did.

634
00:37:06,658 --> 00:37:10,470
Before we proceed, we need precise details

635
00:37:10,528 --> 00:37:13,771
of how you committed the crimes.

636
00:37:14,432 --> 00:37:16,105
Do you understand?

637
00:37:20,138 --> 00:37:21,412
Go ahead.

638
00:37:23,441 --> 00:37:24,647
Well,

639
00:37:25,009 --> 00:37:26,955
I took my father's money and he found out.

640
00:37:27,011 --> 00:37:29,150
Hold on. We said precise details.

641
00:37:29,214 --> 00:37:31,956
The money, how did you find out about it?

642
00:37:33,084 --> 00:37:35,428
What's the hidden context, Doug?

643
00:37:37,222 --> 00:37:39,224
I'm not a competent person.

644
00:37:39,324 --> 00:37:41,167
I can't handle money.

645
00:37:44,162 --> 00:37:46,642
I was getting my finances in order.

646
00:37:46,765 --> 00:37:48,676
I sent away for my credit report.

647
00:37:48,733 --> 00:37:51,009
The bank accounts were listed on the report.

648
00:37:51,069 --> 00:37:53,549
Weren't you afraid your
father'd come after you?

649
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:59,185
I'm still a child, I let fear control me.

650
00:37:59,911 --> 00:38:01,913
Yes, that's the context.

651
00:38:03,515 --> 00:38:06,325
I wanted to use the money for a good purpose.

652
00:38:06,417 --> 00:38:09,125
Something that I'm passionate about.

653
00:38:10,188 --> 00:38:11,792
I wasn't afraid.

654
00:38:13,792 --> 00:38:16,363
So, when your father came after you...

655
00:38:16,628 --> 00:38:21,168
I took his gun, I made Jimmy tie
up Dad and I tied up Jimmy.

656
00:38:21,466 --> 00:38:24,037
And then you kept them in that
motel room for 12 days?

657
00:38:24,102 --> 00:38:26,582
Just you, alone, and those two guys?

658
00:38:29,340 --> 00:38:30,751
I know this one.

659
00:38:31,075 --> 00:38:32,611
I'm not strong.

660
00:38:35,079 --> 00:38:36,717
I'm not powerful.

661
00:38:38,216 --> 00:38:40,059
No one listens to me.

662
00:38:40,919 --> 00:38:43,160
Yes, just me alone.

663
00:38:43,955 --> 00:38:46,561
I made them give up the rest of the money.

664
00:38:46,624 --> 00:38:48,831
I drove them to Dad's office.

665
00:38:53,298 --> 00:38:56,404
And that's when you overcame
your biggest fear.

666
00:39:02,640 --> 00:39:04,586
You changed your way of being.

667
00:39:04,843 --> 00:39:06,015
Yes.

668
00:39:06,177 --> 00:39:09,215
You killed your dad and
transformed your life.

669
00:39:12,684 --> 00:39:14,095
Yes, I did.

670
00:39:14,652 --> 00:39:16,893
And you killed your brother
for the same reason.

671
00:39:16,955 --> 00:39:18,059
Yes.

672
00:39:18,890 --> 00:39:23,270
The brother who loved you,
who watched out for you.

673
00:39:24,095 --> 00:39:25,870
It wasn't real love.

674
00:39:25,964 --> 00:39:27,910
The context wasn't authentic.

675
00:39:27,966 --> 00:39:30,412
He watched out for me out of guilt.

676
00:39:30,635 --> 00:39:32,205
It's old stuff.

677
00:39:33,338 --> 00:39:34,976
It's in the past.

678
00:39:35,373 --> 00:39:37,216
You killed your dad and you let it go.

679
00:39:37,275 --> 00:39:38,345
Yes.

680
00:39:47,785 --> 00:39:49,025
Well,

681
00:39:50,121 --> 00:39:53,591
so then you became everything
that GraceNote promised you.

682
00:39:54,192 --> 00:39:56,968
I mean, like it says right
here in the brochure.

683
00:39:57,028 --> 00:40:00,976
Look, you became the creator
of your own destiny.

684
00:40:03,167 --> 00:40:05,340
That's right. That's right.

685
00:40:05,703 --> 00:40:10,152
Wow, look at you, you're a success story.

686
00:40:12,911 --> 00:40:14,822
Doug's a success story.

687
00:40:16,180 --> 00:40:17,750
Well, Detective...

688
00:40:17,815 --> 00:40:20,455
Well, look at him. He's
the master of his own fate.

689
00:40:20,518 --> 00:40:22,327
Put the past in the past.

690
00:40:22,387 --> 00:40:24,867
He transformed his way of life.

691
00:40:24,923 --> 00:40:26,994
He created his own destiny.

692
00:40:27,058 --> 00:40:29,766
I think he hit the GraceNote trifecta.

693
00:40:29,827 --> 00:40:31,534
Yes, Mr. Fuller?

694
00:40:32,664 --> 00:40:34,871
In a manner of speaking, sure.

695
00:40:35,433 --> 00:40:39,074
So, aren't you gonna use him
as a shining example

696
00:40:40,038 --> 00:40:42,848
of what can be accomplished
with GraceNote's help?

697
00:40:50,748 --> 00:40:52,728
I don't know about that.

698
00:40:52,917 --> 00:40:56,364
But don't you want your
students to follow his example?

699
00:40:58,489 --> 00:41:00,992
I would hope they would find another path.

700
00:41:03,528 --> 00:41:04,598
Oh?

701
00:41:11,269 --> 00:41:12,839
What do you mean?

702
00:41:14,539 --> 00:41:17,611
You mean murder is not the right path?

703
00:41:19,077 --> 00:41:21,182
I would have to say no, Detective.

704
00:41:22,013 --> 00:41:24,084
So, he failed.

705
00:41:25,116 --> 00:41:28,063
Wasn't killing his father a way
to free him from the past?

706
00:41:28,119 --> 00:41:29,393
Of course not.

707
00:41:29,454 --> 00:41:30,865
Do you hear that, Doug?

708
00:41:31,823 --> 00:41:33,359
You failed the course.

709
00:41:33,992 --> 00:41:35,869
You're the same scared loser you were,

710
00:41:35,927 --> 00:41:37,770
when you joined GraceNote.

711
00:41:37,829 --> 00:41:41,003
You... You told me if I killed him,

712
00:41:41,432 --> 00:41:43,571
if I killed him, I'd make the break.

713
00:41:43,634 --> 00:41:45,170
That's not true, Doug.

714
00:41:45,236 --> 00:41:46,806
That's a myth you constructed.

715
00:41:46,871 --> 00:41:48,646
You told me! You...

716
00:41:49,440 --> 00:41:52,046
I did everything you told me, Mr. Fuller.

717
00:41:52,110 --> 00:41:53,111
Everything?

718
00:41:53,177 --> 00:41:56,181
To get the money, all the
money, and to kill them.

719
00:41:56,247 --> 00:41:59,626
He said it would be the last
step to power, to excellence.

720
00:41:59,684 --> 00:42:00,822
That's what you said.

721
00:42:00,885 --> 00:42:02,660
That was a lie, Doug.

722
00:42:05,890 --> 00:42:07,631
That was a big lie.

723
00:42:08,659 --> 00:42:10,297
And that's why you killed Lena.

724
00:42:11,029 --> 00:42:13,373
Did you? Did you do it?

725
00:42:13,431 --> 00:42:17,140
Of course not. She slashed her
wrists, she committed suicide.

726
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:19,738
How do you know that, Mr. Fuller?

727
00:42:24,642 --> 00:42:26,679
Well, I can't say exactly.

728
00:42:26,844 --> 00:42:29,347
She knew someone at GraceNote.
They must've told me there.

729
00:42:29,414 --> 00:42:32,122
The only people we informed
of her death were her parents,

730
00:42:32,183 --> 00:42:34,629
but they weren't told how she died.

731
00:42:35,086 --> 00:42:39,296
Randall Fuller, you are
under arrest for murder.

732
00:42:46,864 --> 00:42:48,844
What did you do to my life?

733
00:42:50,601 --> 00:42:52,274
It wasn't much of a life to begin with.

734
00:42:52,336 --> 00:42:55,749
And I'm not sure the rest of yours
will be something to write home about.

735
00:43:01,913 --> 00:43:04,359
At least Doug learned one
of GraceNote's lessons.

736
00:43:05,416 --> 00:43:07,418
Taking responsibility for his actions.

737
00:43:07,485 --> 00:43:09,431
Something even Randall Fuller couldn't do.

738
00:43:09,487 --> 00:43:12,593
Well, he'll have plenty of opportunity
to learn where he's going.

